cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SD 

This paper discusses the problem of cyberbullying detection in online social networks, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, indicating a potential fit for the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also addresses issues related to scalability and timeliness, which could fall under the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) sub-categories. The paper deals with security and privacy concerns related to cyberbullying, which could be relevant to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel solution for cyberbullying detection, which could be of interest to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category.
